The paper discusses challenges in applying reinforcement learning to real-world problems, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on the challenges of applying RL to real-world problems. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely, as RL is a subfield of AI. cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible categories, as RL has applications in these fields. Finally, cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is a less likely category, but still possible as RL can be used to train agents in multi-agent systems.
